  "description": {
   "en": "The boy runs. Today and tomorrow. Discovering a number of true adventures in the boring daily lives of adults. Walking a tightrope in a wheelbarrow, a March breeze, a wristwatch,   a dirty stray dog...these are the gateways to a world of adventure. Shigeru is a boy who dreams of being a sailor. He successfully infiltrates a ship on a foreign route, but the sailors find him hiding in the hold. \"I wanted to go on my father's ship...\" he said, pointing\nat First Engineer Kumada... \n\nIn addition to the title work \"The Wind in March is 3 Knots'', it includes 5 stories, including \"Independence Festival Night'', \"Takada-kun's Clock'', \"Weakling Koro'', and \"Galaxy Flight'', including a 16-page color manuscript.\n\nA hymn to the boy's soul drawn with a graceful touch by the genius Hisashi Sakaguchi!!"
  },
